  <p style="font-size: 16pt">After months of sleepless nights considering the option and taking the time to hash out details, Jeo Fultano, owner of Endgrain Coffee bar was able to say that the hard work had paid off. <a href="https://www.facebook.com/EndgrainCoffee/posts/2299869843599906" about="_blank">Taking to the Endgrain Coffee Bar Facebook page</a>, Joe announced that the deal was official as of February 28.</p>
  <p style="font-size: 16pt">Pictured here, Joe had signed the papers on the original Second Ave location. Four years ago to the day, the Pitman community were first introduced to Endgrain Coffee Bar. Now, four years on, Endgrain is looking to grow by providing to community with a larger cafe space.</p>
